He was in The Heartbreak Kid. He was in Pineapple Express.

419
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,480
And he would steal these movies with like a scene or two.

420
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:07,340
But he was just a little pop in guy. Yeah.

421
00:36:07,660 --> 00:36:10,000
So when they gave him his own thing.

422
00:36:11,400 --> 00:36:15,980
And for him to like write it and for it to be this fucking good.

423
00:36:17,800 --> 00:36:19,140
It's it's crazy to me.

424
00:36:19,260 --> 00:36:21,280
This that's this is the darkest comedy on the list.

425
00:36:21,300 --> 00:36:22,520
I think Eastbound and Down.

426
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:27,320
I remember at the end of the first season when he abandons his wife at a gas station,

427
00:36:27,720 --> 00:36:31,480
who is his wife, who loves him very much, and they don't really have any problems even.

428
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:35,040
My my ex was like, I don't want to watch this anymore.

429
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:37,200
She was like, I'm not watching the show anymore.

430
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:44,280
It's the show that took the biggest of swings to make this character despicable.

431
00:36:44,620 --> 00:36:48,240
He's beyond David Brent. He's beyond Alan Partridge.

432
00:36:48,300 --> 00:36:52,040
He's beyond all these people. He is a shitty person.

433
00:36:52,500 --> 00:36:55,680
But you love him. You know him.

434
00:36:56,020 --> 00:36:59,660
You in my case, sometimes you are him at your absolute lowest.

435
00:37:01,680 --> 00:37:03,540
He's arrogant. He's angry.

436
00:37:03,540 --> 00:37:08,380
He's he's just in his own head all the time.

437
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:09,720
He can't make connections.

438
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,840
He can't stop his vices.

439
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:13,900
He's a nut.

440
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,600
And I think the first season is the masterpiece.

441
00:37:16,900 --> 00:37:20,760
But the rest of the show is just a bit of a step down.

442
00:37:21,040 --> 00:37:24,300
Love that character. Love his kind of redemption arc.

443
00:37:25,060 --> 00:37:26,580
And I love that.

444
00:37:28,940 --> 00:37:31,140
You know, they'd give him wins and stuff,

445
00:37:31,140 --> 00:37:34,860
but it would always be his win would be like beating the shit out of a child or something.

446
00:37:34,860 --> 00:37:39,000
You know, like it was always with this feeling of like, oh God, you know,

447
00:37:39,920 --> 00:37:41,100
that's one of my favorites.

448
00:37:41,220 --> 00:37:44,960
I don't think we'll ever get a better version of McBride,

449
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:48,380
who is, you know, one of our modern day comedy greats, I think.

450
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:52,880
But that to me, that the time that was running to have something that made me laugh

451
00:37:52,880 --> 00:37:55,340
that hard every Sunday night was just such a gift.

452
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:56,780
And I miss it terribly.

453
00:38:00,140 --> 00:38:06,840
My number five is Ralph Cramden from The Honeymooners,

454
00:38:07,140 --> 00:38:10,340
you know, Jackie Gleason, one of the comedy greats

455
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:14,620
and a sitcom character that he created

456
00:38:15,340 --> 00:38:19,600
that has cemented his footing in sitcom history

457
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:23,360
with a mere 29 episodes of a show.

458
00:38:23,360 --> 00:38:26,420
I mean, it's a pretty incredible thing to do.

459
00:38:27,740 --> 00:38:28,480
But what can I say?

460
00:38:28,940 --> 00:38:30,140
29 episodes of The Honeymooners?

461
00:38:30,340 --> 00:38:32,540
Or 39, I think it was. It's the classic.

462
00:38:32,740 --> 00:38:34,740
I've never seen it, but I thought there was like 400.

463
00:38:35,180 --> 00:38:36,660
No, he did one season.

464
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:40,660
Everything else aside from that one season is the sketches from the show,

465
00:38:40,840 --> 00:38:42,040
from his variety show.

466
00:38:42,700 --> 00:38:46,380
He did once, and then they did terrible reunion movies and things,

467
00:38:46,420 --> 00:38:49,620
but like he did one season, they want it more, and he was like,

468
00:38:49,620 --> 00:38:52,800
nope, we did it. It was great.

469
00:38:52,860 --> 00:38:54,560
We're going to ruin it. And he left it.

470
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:55,720
And that was it.

471
00:38:57,460 --> 00:39:00,020
You know, The Honeymooners is a pretty simple show,

472
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,740
but it's a show that was quite honest

473
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:09,800
and especially for a sitcom in the 50s.

474
00:39:11,100 --> 00:39:12,260
And what can you say?

475
00:39:12,360 --> 00:39:16,900
I mean, Ralph Cramden, it's a recipe for hilarity every time.

476
00:39:16,900 --> 00:39:21,220
You've got a guy who's desperate, who is insecure,

477
00:39:21,740 --> 00:39:24,380
and who is massively explosive,

478
00:39:25,260 --> 00:39:30,140
and you drop him and who has a thirst to try to get rich

479
00:39:30,140 --> 00:39:36,000
and try to figure it out finally for his ship to come in all the time,

480
00:39:36,100 --> 00:39:38,300
just desperately thirsty for that to happen.

481
00:39:38,880 --> 00:39:43,720
And you drop him into situation after situation

482
00:39:43,720 --> 00:39:48,060
where he's going to get prodded and things are not going to go his way,

483
00:39:48,060 --> 00:39:49,520
and then you sit back and watch.

484
00:39:49,620 --> 00:39:51,480
I mean, it is great.

485
00:39:51,720 --> 00:39:55,820
And then you surround him with people that spur that along.

486
00:39:55,960 --> 00:40:00,160
You make his best friend absent -minded and kind of dim with Norton,

487
00:40:01,180 --> 00:40:04,320
but that guy always lands on his feet, and it's not fair.

488
00:40:05,440 --> 00:40:10,080
You have his wife be able to intellectually outsmart him all the time

489
00:40:11,100 --> 00:40:14,320
Alice is the Dorothy of the honeymooner.

490
00:40:14,360 --> 00:40:18,880
She's the one that makes the quips about his weight and his waistline

491
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:21,080
and his job and whatever else.

492
00:40:22,020 --> 00:40:25,680
And people have disparaged the honeymooners and said it inspires violence.

493
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:26,380
It doesn't.

494
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:31,340
Well, he threatens his wife, but he never means it,

495
00:40:31,420 --> 00:40:33,620
and if you watch the show, you know he doesn't mean it.

496
00:40:33,660 --> 00:40:36,540
It's a guy being like, oh, I'd like to not get through that war.

497
00:40:37,360 --> 00:40:40,820
And then she gets in his face, you and what army?

498
00:40:42,280 --> 00:40:45,140
It's all in good fun, in my opinion.

499
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:51,840
And the honeymooners, though not an amazing sitcom, an important one,

500
00:40:53,920 --> 00:40:56,920
and Gleason, a comedy giant, this is his funniest.

501
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:58,940
This is his absolute funniest.

502
00:41:01,340 --> 00:41:04,000
Yeah, I've seen clips, of course, but never a full episode.

503
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,000
I need to.

504
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:10,180
What I learned really is that people just watch,

505
00:41:10,540 --> 00:41:13,480
like somebody last night we were doing a taping and somebody was shocked

506
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:17,300
that I'd never seen a living single, I'd never seen a minute of it.

507
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:23,460
And it's really just whatever your local affiliate plays and reruns is what you see.

508
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:27,280
I never was in an affiliate that showed I Love Lucy, so I've never seen it.

509
00:41:27,860 --> 00:41:32,860
I watched whatever they played, which most of the time was Mama's Family,

510
00:41:32,860 --> 00:41:35,520
I guess because people in Missouri are hicks, but I love Mama's Family.

511
00:41:36,680 --> 00:41:40,060
My number four is Homer Simpson.

512
00:41:41,260 --> 00:41:46,140
I have not watched The Simpsons in 25 years,

513
00:41:47,260 --> 00:41:50,560
but I have seen every episode 10 times.

514
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:55,160
Me and my sister would watch it two or three episodes a night

515
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,420
when it would air in syndication.

516
00:41:56,940 --> 00:42:00,760
And it's easy to forget how groundbreaking this show was.

517
00:42:00,760 --> 00:42:04,220
I was about 10 or something when it premiered,

518
00:42:04,940 --> 00:42:07,660
and George Bush, the President of the United States,

519
00:42:08,320 --> 00:42:13,860
was talking about what a disgraceful role model for kids Bart Simpson was,

520
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:16,420
what a horrible dad Homer Simpson was, etc.

521
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:20,180
The country was up in arms about it.

522
00:42:20,380 --> 00:42:25,320
My parents let me watch The Simpsons, I think just because they saw how brilliant it was.

523
00:42:25,900 --> 00:42:29,520
They wouldn't let me watch it in living color, I think because they were probably slightly racist.

524
00:42:29,520 --> 00:42:33,860
But The Simpsons is a masterpiece.

525
00:42:34,020 --> 00:42:37,640
The first 10 seasons of the show is as funny as animation gets.

526
00:42:37,920 --> 00:42:40,800
It destroys everything in its path, South Park, all these other shows.

527
00:42:41,480 --> 00:42:43,880
For just sheer jokes, the stories are sweet.

528
00:42:44,160 --> 00:42:46,200
I would even go maybe through season 12.

529
00:42:47,080 --> 00:42:55,940
But Homer is, you know, talk about Ramden threatening to beat his wife.

530
00:42:57,100 --> 00:43:01,820
Homer Simpson chokes Bart out as like a recurring bit.

531
00:43:02,100 --> 00:43:08,700
He chokes his son, who is going, you know, that's beyond dark.

532
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:13,000
I just laughed when I was a kid, you know, I didn't think anything of it.

533
00:43:14,040 --> 00:43:19,280
But Homer cannot operate without six beers in him, you know.

534
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:21,780
He is obsessed with drinking. He is obsessed with donuts.

535
00:43:21,780 --> 00:43:26,260
He is horrible at his job, which involves public safety, nuclear health.

536
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:30,440
He is a mess. He is loud. He is stupid.

537
00:43:31,200 --> 00:43:37,740
He is also just unbelievably funny. Dan Castellaneta voiced him.

538
00:43:39,000 --> 00:43:41,600
And, you know, nowadays, who would that have been?

539
00:43:41,820 --> 00:43:44,260
Putty, you know, they'd have to get a name in there.

540
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:46,820
It never would have been Dan Castellaneta.

541
00:43:46,820 --> 00:43:51,440
But it is one of the great voiceover performances of all time.

542
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:55,520
The Simpsons has a deeper character bench than any show that has ever been made.

543
00:43:55,760 --> 00:43:58,820
We're down to the smallest character. They are funny and memorable.

544
00:43:59,540 --> 00:44:03,000
But Homer is the giant that stands atop it all.

545
00:44:03,280 --> 00:44:08,520
He's a legend. He almost slipped my mind because of...

546
00:44:08,520 --> 00:44:11,480
I would cite The Simpsons as one of my top 10 shows of all time.

547
00:44:11,500 --> 00:44:15,580
But it's hard to say that when you haven't seen 25 seasons of it.

548
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:18,400
So that's why Simpsons is in a weird place for me.

549
00:44:18,420 --> 00:44:21,500
But I do think it's the best animated show ever made,

550
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:24,200
and Homer, one of the best animated characters of all time.

551
00:44:25,580 --> 00:44:29,580
I will go with Archie Bunker for number four.

552
00:44:31,180 --> 00:44:34,500
Left him off my list because I knew you would pick him, but certainly a runner -up.

553
00:44:35,280 --> 00:44:39,240
He, you know, look, people, I've talked endlessly on this show

554
00:44:39,240 --> 00:44:43,240
about why I think All in the Family is such an important show,

555
00:44:43,920 --> 00:44:45,920
why I think it's such a masterful show.

556
00:44:46,060 --> 00:44:48,220
It is another show from the Norman Lear universe,

557
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:50,840
the greatest sitcom creator of all time.

558
00:44:52,360 --> 00:44:56,340
And, you know, the nucleus of that universe is All in the Family.

559
00:44:56,520 --> 00:45:00,960
It's a challenging show. It is a show that pulls zero punches.

560
00:45:02,540 --> 00:45:05,860
And whether people are laughing at it for the right reasons or the wrong reasons,

561
00:45:05,980 --> 00:45:08,480
I believe the intention behind the show was pure.

562
00:45:08,480 --> 00:45:14,920
And I believe that it was to show that different families need to function as a unit

563
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:20,620
despite glaringly opposing opinions about things

564
00:45:20,620 --> 00:45:25,880
and people having opinions about those things that are not just unsavory,

565
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:28,500
but at times downright hateful.

566
00:45:29,040 --> 00:45:33,570
And to make a character like Archie Bunker somehow endearing

567
00:45:33,570 --> 00:45:39,570
when he personifies so many awful traits

568
00:45:39,570 --> 00:45:43,990
that needed to be done away with and progressed past

569
00:45:43,990 --> 00:45:48,790
while still having many redeeming qualities of a generation

570
00:45:48,790 --> 00:45:54,570
that knew how to work hard and to provide and do their best for their family.

571
00:45:56,430 --> 00:45:58,930
It's just an amazing character,

572
00:45:59,210 --> 00:46:02,990
and it's played pitch perfectly, of course, by Carol O 'Connor.

573
00:46:03,550 --> 00:46:07,250
The rest of the cast is...

574
00:46:08,070 --> 00:46:10,670
I would say Edith equally excellent.

575
00:46:10,730 --> 00:46:11,850
So maybe this is a tie.

576
00:46:12,350 --> 00:46:18,170
Edith equally excellent and equally portrayed brilliantly by Maureen Stapleton.

577
00:46:18,390 --> 00:46:20,470
Was it Maureen or Jeanne? Is Maureen...

578
00:46:20,470 --> 00:46:22,390
How do you get the Stapletons mixed up?

579
00:46:24,090 --> 00:46:24,370
Jeanne.

580
00:46:24,790 --> 00:46:26,010
It's Jeanne Stapleton.

581
00:46:26,150 --> 00:46:28,290
Maureen Stapleton is from Johnny Dangerously.

582
00:46:28,390 --> 00:46:29,790
But they're sisters, right?

583
00:46:29,990 --> 00:46:32,370
And she's from Michael. They're not sisters.

584
00:46:32,370 --> 00:46:33,590
I remember looking it up.

585
00:46:33,970 --> 00:46:40,050
Okay. Anyway, the two of them together are just a...

586
00:46:40,050 --> 00:46:40,930
Yeah, they're unrelated.

587
00:46:41,610 --> 00:46:42,290
That's wild.

588
00:46:42,910 --> 00:46:46,010
Just a brilliant, brilliant sitcom team.

589
00:46:48,210 --> 00:46:56,070
And her dim -witted innocence up against his pointed condescension,

590
00:46:57,270 --> 00:46:59,430
it is a perfect fit.

591
00:46:59,430 --> 00:47:05,650
And the fact that he believes he is smart and she is unaware that she isn't

592
00:47:06,330 --> 00:47:13,430
allows for the stage to be set for her to often outwit him unintentionally.

593
00:47:15,750 --> 00:47:19,450
And watching that exchange, watching that battle happen,

594
00:47:19,510 --> 00:47:23,830
and watching him lose is quite brilliant.

595
00:47:25,250 --> 00:47:28,070
And again, characters that you could take out of this show

596
00:47:28,070 --> 00:47:32,010
and plop into anything and they would still be as robust.

597
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:39,830
Challenging, brilliant, hilarious Archie and Edith Barker.

598
00:47:42,290 --> 00:47:43,590
I love it.

599
00:47:44,830 --> 00:47:52,430
My number three is Larry David himself on Curb Your Enthusiasm.

600
00:47:53,390 --> 00:47:56,110
The final season is rapidly approaching.

601
00:47:57,910 --> 00:48:02,390
Just an unbelievably consistent comedy show.

602
00:48:02,950 --> 00:48:06,850
I was working at Blockbuster Video when Curb Your Enthusiasm was coming out.

603
00:48:07,090 --> 00:48:11,730
And I was like, you might have seen Larry David at an awards show or something,

604
00:48:11,770 --> 00:48:13,410
but we didn't know anything about the guy.

605
00:48:13,690 --> 00:48:19,870
And I was like, the writer of Seinfeld is going to have his own show?

606
00:48:22,030 --> 00:48:25,290
I thought, well, how many writers can actually perform?

607
00:48:25,850 --> 00:48:28,530
A. What is he thinking?

608
00:48:28,670 --> 00:48:32,330
He doesn't look like a guy who should be on television.

609
00:48:32,430 --> 00:48:34,330
He's too old. He's too ugly.

610
00:48:34,570 --> 00:48:37,890
He's too nerdy, whatever you want to say.

611
00:48:37,910 --> 00:48:43,030
He just doesn't have the charisma that you would think you would need to lead a TV show.

612
00:48:43,830 --> 00:48:45,110
Of course, I knew he was brilliant.

613
00:48:45,310 --> 00:48:47,390
He created my favorite sitcom of all time.

614
00:48:47,390 --> 00:48:50,370
But I certainly didn't have the highest of hopes.

615
00:48:52,390 --> 00:48:59,590
And then for it to be arguably every bit as funny as Seinfeld,

616
00:49:00,110 --> 00:49:04,290
certainly in the first 10 years, you know, they've had a few seasons that were still good,

617
00:49:04,290 --> 00:49:06,490
but maybe dipped a little bit.

618
00:49:07,890 --> 00:49:11,750
The first few years of the show, I was like, these plots are just as good as Seinfeld.

619
00:49:11,910 --> 00:49:16,030
No one has come up with just more genius plots over time than that man.

620
00:49:16,630 --> 00:49:21,310
And he was doing for an app on Seinfeld for plots that would combine.

621
00:49:22,970 --> 00:49:24,850
So I'm a huge fan.

622
00:49:25,070 --> 00:49:32,870
And obviously the improv aspect of the show makes it a little different than everything else on the list.

623
00:49:33,550 --> 00:49:39,270
But who is really funnier than, you know, on that show?

624
00:49:39,610 --> 00:49:43,190
You'd be hard pressed. And he's the misanthrope.

625
00:49:43,310 --> 00:49:45,910
He's the angry guy. He's the guy who gets into fights.

626
00:49:45,910 --> 00:49:47,990
He's the guy who says everything we want to say.

627
00:49:48,310 --> 00:49:50,970
That's not necessarily the freshest character trope.

628
00:49:51,230 --> 00:49:53,730
But my God, does he put his own spin on it.

629
00:49:53,790 --> 00:49:56,230
I had never seen anything like that before.

630
00:49:56,750 --> 00:50:01,150
And yet it has the feel of Seinfeld. That's what makes it so great.

631
00:50:01,210 --> 00:50:06,670
He did something that has the feel, but is a completely different thing.

632
00:50:07,530 --> 00:50:15,390
And to be a writer who is now a yearly nominee for best actor at the, you know,

633
00:50:15,390 --> 00:50:20,090
this man is a talent like none other. He's one of the great humans of all time.

634
00:50:21,010 --> 00:50:24,070
I am remorning the day Larry David passes away.

635
00:50:25,210 --> 00:50:27,850
And Curb Enthusiasm is one of the best comedies ever made.

636
00:50:32,190 --> 00:50:35,710
He was my number three as well.

637
00:50:36,810 --> 00:50:38,710
And my number two was David Brent.

638
00:50:39,330 --> 00:50:41,410
All right. I'm going to jump to my number two.

639
00:50:42,310 --> 00:50:45,310
But I will add to what you just said.

640
00:50:48,770 --> 00:50:52,450
He is I had to pop a Tic Tac because my sugar is dropping.

641
00:50:53,550 --> 00:50:57,390
All right. It's a fun thing as you get old, you sort of get lightheaded for no reason.

642
00:50:58,790 --> 00:51:05,650
Anyway, but one thing I'd add to Larry David is it's the most that's my Chandler.

643
00:51:05,770 --> 00:51:09,170
He's the most relatable person I've ever seen on television.

644
00:51:09,170 --> 00:51:11,950
I've never felt more shoes of somebody.

645
00:51:12,210 --> 00:51:18,470
Yeah, 100 percent to the I can't let things go.

646
00:51:19,810 --> 00:51:21,250
Yeah, you've heard it on the show.

647
00:51:21,350 --> 00:51:24,350
I mean, he's me now, although so many people say they're Larry David.

648
00:51:24,370 --> 00:51:26,370
That's the beauty of it. Everyone says that's me.

649
00:51:26,610 --> 00:51:29,090
Many people are like, no, it's not fucking you.

650
00:51:29,090 --> 00:51:31,710
I can say that it is actually me.

651
00:51:32,170 --> 00:51:33,670
No, I feel the same.

652
00:51:33,750 --> 00:51:38,230
And I think you've got the explosive anger more than I do where you'll actually yell at people and call them out.

